  "siteName": "Google DeepMind Blog",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <uni-article-speakable style=\"height: 55px; margin-bottom: 36px; display: block;\" page-title=\"Nano Banana 2: Combining Pro capabilities with lightning\\u002Dfast speed\" listen-to-article=\"Listen to article\" data-date-modified=\"2026-02-26T16:02:08.759898+00:00\" data-tracking-ids=\"G-HGNBTNCHCQ,G-6NKTLKV14N\" data-voice-list=\"en.ioh-pngnat:Cyan,en.usb-pngnat:Lime\" data-script-src=\"https://www.gstatic.com/readaloud/player/web/api/js/api.js\" data-highlight-mode=\"word-over-paragraph\">\n   <!---->\n   <div id=\"uni-article-speakable\">\n    <!--?lit$6598226066$-->\n    <span width=\"14px\"> \n     <svg width=\"24px\" viewBox=\"0 0 66 66\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"uni-spinner uni-spinner--small\">\n      <circle class=\"loader-path\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"7\" cx=\"33\" cy=\"33\" r=\"25\"></circle>\n     </svg> \n    </span>\n   </div>\n  </uni-article-speakable>\n  <!--article text-->\n  <div class=\"module--text module--text__article\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           &quot;module_name&quot;: &quot;Paragraph&quot;,\n           &quot;section_header&quot;: &quot;Nano Banana 2: Combining Pro capabilities with lightning\\u002Dfast speed&quot;\n         }\">\n   <div class=\"uni-paragraph article-paragraph\" data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-component-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"rich-text\">\n     <p data-block-key=\"78m38\" class=\"drop-cap\">In August of last year, our Gemini Image model, <a href=\"https://blog.google/products-and-platforms/products/gemini/updated-image-editing-model/\">Nano Banana</a>, became a <a href=\"https://blog.google/products-and-platforms/products/gemini/nano-banana-google-trends-2025/\">viral sensation</a>, redefining image generation and editing. Then in November, we released <a href=\"https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/products/nano-banana-pro/\">Nano Banana Pro</a>, offering users advanced intelligence and studio-quality creative control. Today, we’re bringing the best of both worlds to users across Google.</p>\n     <p data-block-key=\"191b\">Introducing Nano Banana 2 (Gemini 3.1 Flash Image), our latest state-of-the-art image model. Now you can get the advanced world knowledge, quality and reasoning you love in Nano Banana Pro, at lightning-fast speed.</p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"module--text module--text__article\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           &quot;module_name&quot;: &quot;Paragraph&quot;,\n           &quot;section_header&quot;: &quot;Nano Banana 2: Combining Pro capabilities with lightning\\u002Dfast speed&quot;\n         }\">\n   <div class=\"uni-paragraph article-paragraph\" data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-component-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"rich-text\">\n     <h2 data-block-key=\"78m38\">Intelligence and visual quality at Flash speed</h2>\n     <p data-block-key=\"2eg6u\">Nano Banana 2 brings the high-speed intelligence of Gemini Flash to visual generation, making rapid edits and iteration possible. It makes once-exclusive Pro features accessible to a wider audience, including:</p>\n     <ul>\n      <li data-block-key=\"ci6kk\"><b>Advanced world knowledge:</b> The model pulls from Gemini’s real-world knowledge base, and is powered by real-time information and images from web search to more accurately render specific subjects. This deep understanding also helps you create infographics, turn notes into diagrams and generate data visualizations.</li>\n      <li data-block-key=\"nql7\"><b>Precision text rendering and translation</b>: Nano Banana 2 allows you to generate accurate, legible text for marketing mockups or greeting cards. You can even translate and localize text within an image to share your ideas globally.</li>\n     </ul>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n  <uni-image-carousel section-header=\"Nano Banana 2: Combining Pro capabilities with lightning\\u002Dfast speed\" images=\"[\n    \n      {\n        \n          \n          \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/wm-c2a77d45-6afd-4d2e-ae5b-3f1e.max-768x768.format-webp.webp&quot;,&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/wm-c2a77d45-6afd-4d2e-ae5b-3f1.max-1376x768.format-webp.webp&quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;High\\u002Dquality flat lay photography of a DIY infographic explaining the water cycle on a clean, light gray textured background with hand\\u002Ddrawn black arrows to guide the viewer through the process&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: false,\n        &quot;autoplay&quot;: true,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;&quot;,\n        &quot;audioDescriptiveVideoURL&quot;: &quot;&quot;,\n        &quot;videoTracks&quot;: [\n          \n        ]\n      },\n    \n      {\n        \n          \n          \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/wm-15220c99-824b-4040-a8bd-eb7e.max-768x768.format-webp.webp&quot;,&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/wm-15220c99-824b-4040-a8bd-eb7.max-1376x768.format-webp.webp&quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;A three\\u002Dpanel comic\\u002Dstyle infographic in 16:9 aspect ratio comparing Cumulus, Stratus, and Cirrus clouds, each shown in a dramatic sky with a bold label&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: false,\n        &quot;autoplay&quot;: true,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;&quot;,\n        &quot;audioDescriptiveVideoURL&quot;: &quot;&quot;,\n        &quot;videoTracks&quot;: [\n          \n        ]\n      },\n    \n      {\n        \n          \n          \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/DH_gemini-image__grounded-ima.max-1080x1080.format-webp.webp&quot;,&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/DH_gemini-image__grounded-ima.max-1080x1080.format-webp.webp&quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;A 16:9 aspect ratio image of Museum Clos Lucé rendered in the style of bright\\u002Dcolored Synthetic Cubism without any text&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: false,\n        &quot;autoplay&quot;: true,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;&quot;,\n        &quot;audioDescriptiveVideoURL&quot;: &quot;&quot;,\n        &quot;videoTracks&quot;: [\n          \n        ]\n      },\n    \n      {\n        \n          \n          \n          &quot;src&quot;: [&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/gemini-image_localisation_1_l.max-1080x1080.format-webp.webp&quot;,&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/gemini-image_localisation_1_l.max-1080x1080.format-webp.webp&quot;],\n        \n        &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;2 images on a white background: First, A cinematic close\\u002Dup of an intricately illustrated sign made of recycled material featuring local birds and flowers and text that reads \\u0022Native Wildlife: Please Observe from a Distance\\u0022 against a soft blur of green foliage.  Second, a version of the \\u0022Native Wildlife\\u0022 sign localized for an Indian setting, with all text translated into Hindi&quot;,\n        &quot;isVideo&quot;: false,\n        &quot;autoplay&quot;: true,\n        &quot;videoTitle&quot;: &quot;&quot;,\n        &quot;audioDescriptiveVideoURL&quot;: &quot;&quot;,\n        &quot;videoTracks&quot;: [\n          \n        ]\n      }\n    \n  ]\">\n   <!---->\n   <div class=\"article-module ga4-carousel\" data-component=\"uni-image-carousel\" data-analytics-module=\"{&quot;module_name&quot;:&quot;Article Carousel&quot;,&quot;section_header&quot;:&quot;Nano Banana 2: Combining Pro capabilities with lightning-fast speed&quot;}\" data-component-initialized=\"true\">\n    <div class=\"article-carousel\" aria-roledescription=\"carousel\">\n     <!--?lit$6598226066$-->\n